WEBVTT

00:10.552 --> 00:11.803
♪ You could do it solo ♪

00:11.803 --> 00:13.889
♪ But then you'd be all by yourself ♪

00:13.889 --> 00:16.308
♪ Yo! So it'd be more fun
To share this one ♪

00:16.308 --> 00:17.893
♪ With someone else ♪

00:17.893 --> 00:21.647
♪ Together we will soar
Across the sky and beyond ♪

00:21.647 --> 00:22.814
♪ So turn up your voice ♪

00:23.690 --> 00:25.567
♪ Stand up and sing along! ♪

00:25.567 --> 00:26.860
♪ All different voices ♪

00:26.860 --> 00:27.861
♪ Everybody now! ♪

00:27.861 --> 00:29.238
♪ Our melodies ringing ♪

00:29.238 --> 00:31.156
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪

00:31.156 --> 00:33.242
♪ Yeah, we're livin' in harmony ♪

00:33.242 --> 00:36.870
♪ Our song is much stronger
With every Troll singing ♪

00:36.870 --> 00:39.456
♪ We're livin' in harmony ♪♪

00:40.999 --> 00:42.960
♪

00:44.586 --> 00:45.629
HOLLY:
Huh.

00:45.629 --> 00:46.588
VAL:
Ha. Ugh.

00:47.464 --> 00:48.590
HOLLY:
Huh. Hmm.

00:48.590 --> 00:50.092
VAL: Ugh.
HOLLY: ¡Ha yah!

00:50.801 --> 00:52.010
‐ Ha. Ah.

00:52.010 --> 00:52.844
‐ Ha.

00:53.804 --> 00:56.765
‐ Final moves of the game. Do or die.

00:57.224 --> 01:01.144
This is the moment when Troll Chess
can be absolutely brutal.

01:01.979 --> 01:03.230
HOLLY:
Hyah!

01:04.356 --> 01:05.691
Bishop befriends knight.

01:06.066 --> 01:06.900
‐ Ugh.

01:07.568 --> 01:09.027
Yeah, you got me.

01:09.987 --> 01:10.821
<i>Hugmate.</i>

01:11.071 --> 01:12.698
TROLLS:
Aw...

01:13.949 --> 01:16.743
‐ Man! I can't put my finger
on why exactly,

01:16.743 --> 01:19.830
but that was the best game of Trolls chess
I've ever played.

01:19.830 --> 01:20.872
‐ Well...

01:20.872 --> 01:24.042
that's 'cuz these chess pieces
are fresh, sugar.

01:24.501 --> 01:26.461
‐ "Fresh"? Like they were just made?

01:26.795 --> 01:31.800
‐ Oh, no, no, we Country Western Trolls
don't make our gamin' pieces...

01:32.259 --> 01:33.885
We grow 'em!

01:33.885 --> 01:35.554
[ sheep bleating ]

01:35.554 --> 01:37.806
<i>Like russet dominoes.</i>

01:39.433 --> 01:40.559
<i>Jackfruits.</i>

01:43.937 --> 01:45.689
<i>And checkers on the cob.</i>

01:46.732 --> 01:48.650
[ laughing ]

01:48.650 --> 01:50.694
[ crowd gasps ]

01:50.694 --> 01:52.738
‐ Yep, it's one of the reasons

01:52.738 --> 01:55.449
I'm so proud to be
a Country Western Troll.

01:55.449 --> 01:58.785
We make a point to cultivate
games the natural way.

01:59.202 --> 02:03.540
And as we all know,
the natural way is the best way.

02:03.915 --> 02:04.958
SKY:
Inaccurate.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.001
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

02:06.001 --> 02:07.544
HOLLY:
Sky Toronto?

02:07.919 --> 02:10.714
I'm sorry, you'll need to say that again.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.342
I'm not sure I heard you right.

02:13.717 --> 02:15.177
‐ Oh. My apologies.

02:16.720 --> 02:19.556
<i>I said your statement was inaccurate!</i>

02:19.973 --> 02:21.224
[ grunt ]

02:21.558 --> 02:25.771
Of course, it goes without saying,
I deeply respect the Country Tribe.

02:25.771 --> 02:28.148
But to suggest
you can produce games better

02:28.148 --> 02:31.276
than the machines in my factory,
well, it's laughable.

02:32.361 --> 02:33.278
‐ Ha!

02:33.278 --> 02:34.112
‐ See?

02:34.571 --> 02:35.989
[ grunt ]

02:35.989 --> 02:37.366
‐ Easy, Holly.

02:37.366 --> 02:40.577
Everyone's entitled
to their own opinion, right?

02:40.994 --> 02:42.663
‐ Very true, Queen Poppy.

02:42.954 --> 02:45.582
But given that I'm currently
stating a fact,

02:45.582 --> 02:47.000
it's also very irrelevant.

02:47.376 --> 02:49.086
[ grunt ]

02:49.086 --> 02:50.212
‐ Hoo, boy.

02:50.629 --> 02:53.340
‐ You see,
the Trolls in my R&D department

02:53.340 --> 02:56.718
develop inventions
that practically revolutionize

02:56.718 --> 02:58.303
fun production everyday.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.306
‐ As you're about to see,

03:01.306 --> 03:05.102
our new prototype
does the work of 50 Trolls

03:05.102 --> 03:06.520
with the push of a button.

03:07.187 --> 03:08.063
[ beep ]

03:19.741 --> 03:21.451
‐ Hmm. Not bad.

03:21.743 --> 03:25.122
But isn't there a way the machine
could push the button for me?

03:25.580 --> 03:26.998
‐ Ooh!
‐ Ooh!

03:27.249 --> 03:29.292
‐ Yes, my factory is fast,

03:29.292 --> 03:33.004
efficient and, while your crops
would wither in minutes in the snow,

03:33.004 --> 03:35.924
my production is unaffected by winter.

03:36.174 --> 03:37.217
HOLLY:
Winter?

03:37.217 --> 03:39.344
We'll have the crops harvested by then.

03:39.344 --> 03:40.595
Winter ain't for months.

03:40.971 --> 03:43.181
‐ Actually, Holly...

03:43.181 --> 03:46.435
one teensy correction
about the Pop Troll's calendar.

03:46.435 --> 03:47.436
You see...

03:47.727 --> 03:51.064
For us, winter happens all in one day
and is coming any time now, bye!

03:51.064 --> 03:51.898
‐ What?

03:52.149 --> 03:54.568
<i>‐ She said:</i>
<i>"Winter happens all in one day</i>

03:54.568 --> 03:56.987
<i>and is coming any time now, bye."</i>

03:57.529 --> 03:59.239
‐ I heard what she said!

03:59.239 --> 04:01.908
Now listen, Sky, and listen good.

04:02.200 --> 04:04.119
I don't care how soon winter's comin',

04:04.119 --> 04:06.663
we're gonna harvest every one
of them crops!

04:06.663 --> 04:09.541
'Cuz we are Country Western Trolls,

04:09.541 --> 04:14.171
and we got the grit and resourcefulness
to do anything a factory can do...

04:14.671 --> 04:16.047
only better.

04:16.965 --> 04:17.799
‐ Hm.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.552
Well, I wish you the best of luck.

04:20.760 --> 04:24.055
That said, my position on the matter
remains unchanged.

04:25.974 --> 04:26.808
<i>Thank you!</i>

04:29.311 --> 04:30.729
[ grunt ]

04:30.729 --> 04:33.398
‐ Country Western Tribe, round up!

04:33.982 --> 04:35.317
[ crowd muttering ]

04:35.317 --> 04:38.570
Y'all, if we're gonna save these crops
and show Sky what's what,

04:38.862 --> 04:42.491
we need to figure out exactly
how much time we got before snowfall.

04:42.783 --> 04:43.867
‐ "Exactly"?

04:44.242 --> 04:45.285
How will you do that?

04:45.660 --> 04:47.662
‐ By using the Country Western tribe's

04:47.662 --> 04:50.707
most sophisticated
weather predicting device.

04:50.707 --> 04:51.792
[ whistle ]

04:51.792 --> 04:52.584
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

04:52.918 --> 04:55.170
[ trolls gasp ]

04:55.170 --> 04:57.631
HOLLY:
Gust Tumbleweed's thumb.

04:59.883 --> 05:00.926
‐ Wow!

05:02.886 --> 05:04.679
‐ Hm...

05:05.388 --> 05:09.100
We got 2 weeks, 3 days,
10 hours and 47 minutes!

05:09.100 --> 05:11.436
‐ Yeehaw!
‐ Yeehaw!

05:11.436 --> 05:13.814
‐ Hot dang! We can work with that!

05:14.064 --> 05:16.733
If'n we get a little help
with all the labor...?

05:16.983 --> 05:19.027
‐ Oh, I think we know some Trolls

05:19.110 --> 05:22.197
who aren't afraid of a little hard work,
right everyone?

05:22.280 --> 05:23.240
‐ Right!
‐ Right!

05:24.199 --> 05:25.617
‐ K, cool, have fun with that!

05:26.284 --> 05:27.369
‐ Val?
‐ Val?

05:27.369 --> 05:30.080
‐ Oh, you didn't think I meant me,
did you?

05:30.080 --> 05:31.706
Pfft, that's hilarious.

05:31.706 --> 05:33.750
[ laughing ]

05:34.334 --> 05:35.502
Aw, man, so good.

05:35.794 --> 05:36.920
[ trolls sigh ]

05:39.798 --> 05:40.632
‐ Woo hoo!

05:41.383 --> 05:43.468
Keep it up, y'all, you're doin' great!

05:44.427 --> 05:47.347
Just remember to separate
the good crops from the bad.

05:47.722 --> 05:50.308
See how this six‐sided die's
grown a seven on it?

05:50.767 --> 05:51.768
That's bad.

05:52.185 --> 05:56.147
‐ Yes, I see,
this one has a square root of 23.

05:56.857 --> 05:58.692
‐ This one just says:

05:58.692 --> 06:02.028
"Who was the third mayor
of Lonesome Flats?"

06:02.362 --> 06:03.238
[ sighs ]

06:03.238 --> 06:06.658
‐ Yep, it musta crosspollinated
with the trivia cards.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.034
‐ Mm‐hm.
‐ Mm‐hm.

06:08.326 --> 06:09.536
‐ That would make sense.

06:10.662 --> 06:13.623
HOLLY:
Now, we need a place to store the harvest.

06:13.874 --> 06:16.209
So, while we Country Trolls
work the fields,

06:16.209 --> 06:19.379
y'all are gonna have
an ol' fashion barn raisin'!

06:19.379 --> 06:20.213
[ gasp ]

06:20.213 --> 06:21.047
‐ Holly!

06:21.423 --> 06:24.175
You expect me to build a barn?

06:24.801 --> 06:27.137
Also, what's a barn?

06:27.429 --> 06:28.597
[ chuckle ]

06:28.597 --> 06:30.473
‐ It's easy, y'all!

06:30.473 --> 06:32.392
As any Country Troll will tell you,

06:32.642 --> 06:35.562
all you need to raise a barn
is a little know how...

06:36.021 --> 06:37.981
and a lot of music.

06:39.024 --> 06:40.317
[ laughing ]

06:40.317 --> 06:44.195
♪

06:44.195 --> 06:45.614
♪ Come one, come all ♪

06:45.614 --> 06:47.824
♪ Y'all know that we gon get it done ♪

06:47.824 --> 06:49.492
♪ And if we're singing ♪

06:49.492 --> 06:51.494
♪ Then you know we're having fun ♪

06:51.911 --> 06:55.707
♪ Let's work together
To the rhythm of our song ♪

06:55.707 --> 06:58.793
♪ Now everyone hammer along ♪

06:58.793 --> 07:01.546
♪ Cause it takes hugs
Sweat, tears and glitter ♪

07:01.546 --> 07:03.089
♪ And heaps of heart ♪

07:03.089 --> 07:05.467
♪ Together we'll deliver ♪

07:05.467 --> 07:07.052
♪ We're working hard ♪

07:07.052 --> 07:09.387
♪ Hugs, sweat, tears and glitter ♪

07:09.387 --> 07:10.805
♪ To get it done ♪

07:10.805 --> 07:14.392
♪ We're sweating but y'all know
We're having fun ♪

07:14.392 --> 07:18.021
♪ We're sweating but y'all know
We're having fun ♪♪

07:19.856 --> 07:21.066
[ trolls scream ]

07:22.525 --> 07:23.360
‐ Uh...

07:23.735 --> 07:28.448
K, how 'bout a little music
and a lotta know how?

07:28.782 --> 07:30.450
‐ Yeah, totally.

07:33.119 --> 07:34.037
[ sigh ]

07:34.412 --> 07:35.914
‐ Now that's a thing of beauty.

07:36.373 --> 07:37.749
‐ It sure is.

07:37.999 --> 07:40.085
But nothin' is gonna be as beautiful

07:40.085 --> 07:42.295
as the look on Sky Toronto's face

07:42.295 --> 07:44.798
when he sees
how much progress we've made.

07:45.382 --> 07:47.967
And we still have
a whole week left before winter!

07:47.967 --> 07:50.720
[ wind blows ]

07:50.720 --> 07:51.805
[ gasp ]

07:53.640 --> 07:54.474
Uh‐oh.

07:54.849 --> 07:58.103
[ wind blows ]

07:58.103 --> 08:00.647
[ humming ]

08:01.231 --> 08:02.857
‐ Huh?
‐ Ohmyguh?

08:03.191 --> 08:04.401
[ thunder ]

08:04.401 --> 08:06.277
‐ No. No, it can't be.

08:06.611 --> 08:09.906
It feels like winter's comin',
but Gust said...

08:10.615 --> 08:11.533
‐ I...

08:11.533 --> 08:13.451
I think I used the wrong thumb.

08:13.827 --> 08:14.786
[ gasp ]

08:15.453 --> 08:16.788
‐ Harvest, y'all!

08:16.788 --> 08:19.332
Harvest like the wind!

08:20.208 --> 08:21.126
‐ Ohmyguh!

08:21.626 --> 08:25.463
[ screaming ]

08:25.463 --> 08:29.426
[ grunting ]

08:29.426 --> 08:32.721
[ Demo screaming ]

08:32.721 --> 08:34.556
[ trolls screaming ]

08:34.556 --> 08:36.266
‐ Hurry!
‐ Hurry!

08:36.266 --> 08:38.309
[ panting ]

08:38.309 --> 08:39.144
[ scream ]

08:39.853 --> 08:45.900
[ screaming ]

08:47.652 --> 08:51.156
‐ Well, I'm sorry for their misfortune
but I tried to warn them,

08:51.656 --> 08:53.742
the factory way is the best way.

08:53.992 --> 08:57.162
Take these factory‐made
playing cards, for example.

08:57.162 --> 09:00.498
Why, I don't remember a game
ever being this much fun...

09:02.083 --> 09:02.959
Actually...

09:03.668 --> 09:05.420
I really don't remember.

09:06.004 --> 09:07.714
Wait, where did you get these?

09:09.049 --> 09:11.092
You! How did you get in here?

09:11.384 --> 09:13.845
‐ Yeah, I gave your assistant
the night off.

09:14.137 --> 09:16.097
And those playing cards...

09:16.556 --> 09:18.099
they're not from your factory.

09:18.391 --> 09:19.225
[ gasp ]

09:19.893 --> 09:23.813
[ screaming ]

09:23.813 --> 09:27.108
‐ No! No, y'all!
We gotta settle down before the snow‐‐

09:28.443 --> 09:29.569
Gah!

09:29.569 --> 09:31.237
[ trolls screaming ]

09:32.739 --> 09:34.741
[ trolls mumbling ]

09:35.116 --> 09:37.202
[ grunting ]

09:37.202 --> 09:38.745
‐ No, no, no.

09:38.745 --> 09:42.207
There was so much fun
to be harvested out in them fields,

09:43.041 --> 09:45.418
and it's all gonna wither away in minutes.

09:45.418 --> 09:47.003
[ sigh ]

09:47.295 --> 09:49.380
SKY:
Well, that's more time than we need!

09:53.927 --> 09:54.761
‐ What?

09:55.595 --> 09:57.889
<i>‐ I said that's more than we need!</i>

09:58.515 --> 10:01.434
I realize she was actually
just expressing her surprise,

10:01.434 --> 10:03.812
but I find this megaphone bit
mildly amusing.

10:04.521 --> 10:06.815
‐ B‐but what are you doing here?

10:07.482 --> 10:09.484
‐ Helping with the harvest, of course!

10:09.484 --> 10:11.486
Your friend Val invaded my office

10:11.486 --> 10:15.115
and made me see just how special
your game crops really are.

10:15.865 --> 10:16.950
‐ Val...

10:16.950 --> 10:18.451
you did that for me?

10:20.286 --> 10:21.454
‐ Indeed she did.

10:21.788 --> 10:24.457
It was both aggressive and unsettling.

10:24.791 --> 10:25.708
[ chuckle ]

10:25.708 --> 10:28.294
You see, Holly,
while factory fun production

10:28.294 --> 10:29.671
has many advantages,

10:29.671 --> 10:33.716
I now realize there's a richness
to the Country Western way,

10:33.716 --> 10:36.803
a fun‐of‐the‐earth quality
that can't be manufactured.

10:37.303 --> 10:38.763
And I came here to say...

10:40.223 --> 10:41.057
‐ I was wrong.

10:41.683 --> 10:45.311
‐ So, I had the Trolls in R&D
modify this for the snow!

10:45.311 --> 10:46.312
[ beep ]

11:00.034 --> 11:00.994
[ cheer ]

11:00.994 --> 11:03.496
‐ Yeehaw!
‐ Yeehaw!

11:04.789 --> 11:10.753
♪

11:11.588 --> 11:13.298
‐ Well, looking at all this,

11:13.298 --> 11:16.467
it feels silly that we disagreed
over whose way is better.

11:16.467 --> 11:20.972
‐ Yeah, when it's so clear that it's best
when we combine our ways together.

11:22.557 --> 11:24.517
[ chuckle ]

11:24.517 --> 11:27.103
‐ I hate to quibble with you, fine Trolls,

11:27.103 --> 11:31.065
but the best way is to use
a Funk Tribe game replicator.

11:34.861 --> 11:36.779
‐ Yeah, so his way is much better.

11:37.030 --> 11:37.947
‐ Oh, no question.

11:40.158 --> 11:42.160
♪

11:45.914 --> 11:51.211
[ laughing ]

11:53.087 --> 11:55.715
‐ Step right up, Trolls! Step right up!

11:55.715 --> 11:57.383
To the Tunnel of Friendship!

11:58.176 --> 11:59.093
Say...

11:59.093 --> 12:01.387
you two looking to celebrate,
commemorate,

12:01.387 --> 12:04.807
corroborate and articulate
your one‐of‐a‐kind special bond?

12:04.807 --> 12:06.142
‐ You know it, bro!

12:06.142 --> 12:07.101
‐ Indeed.

12:07.477 --> 12:10.188
‐ Well, if that isn't the cat's pajamas,

12:10.188 --> 12:12.482
the cat's meow, or a third cat metaphor

12:12.482 --> 12:14.859
that stands for something better
than average!

12:15.401 --> 12:18.029
Oh, but hold the phone, friends,

12:18.029 --> 12:19.989
the tunnel's booked solid 'til...

12:19.989 --> 12:22.200
[ whistle ]

12:22.575 --> 12:23.910
...tomorrow at noon?

12:23.910 --> 12:25.453
‐ We'll take it.
‐ We'll take it.

12:25.453 --> 12:26.955
STRIPE:
Here you go, friends!

12:27.664 --> 12:30.208
‐ Minuet, Synth? Did I hear you, right?

12:30.583 --> 12:32.335
You're riding the tunnel together?

12:32.585 --> 12:33.878
‐ You heard correctly!

12:33.878 --> 12:38.758
‐ Haha! That's some grade‐A
eavesdroppin', Popp‐ay!

12:39.092 --> 12:40.969
‐ Well, hot dang, y'all!

12:40.969 --> 12:44.722
Goin' through the tunnel
is a special moment in any friendship!

12:45.139 --> 12:48.601
Oh, Poppy girl, remember our ride?

12:49.102 --> 12:51.104
‐ The gentle rock of the boat...

12:51.104 --> 12:54.190
‐ Our BFF song playin'
on the loudspeaker...

12:54.440 --> 12:57.402
‐ Oh, seems like it was only yesterday.

12:57.777 --> 12:59.862
‐ Mm, 'cuz it was.

13:00.113 --> 13:01.656
[ sigh ]

13:01.906 --> 13:04.284
‐ Ugh, so enchanting.

13:04.617 --> 13:08.288
I only hope our ride
is as special as all that.

13:08.288 --> 13:09.872
‐ Oh, I know it will be.

13:10.206 --> 13:14.043
But, to be honest, I didn't realize
you two had gotten so close.

13:14.043 --> 13:15.211
[ chuckle ]

13:15.211 --> 13:18.631
‐ Yeah, we are kind of an unlikely mashup.

13:18.923 --> 13:23.428
‐ But we've found that we open up
one another to new experiences!

13:25.555 --> 13:27.056
‐ Enchanté...

13:28.933 --> 13:30.268
‐ Back at you, bro!

13:31.686 --> 13:32.520
Blam!

13:33.855 --> 13:35.064
Aight, y'all.

13:35.064 --> 13:38.109
Backing me up on the mic,
make some noise for...

13:38.109 --> 13:40.361
Synth!

13:40.903 --> 13:46.909
[ singing opera ]

13:47.785 --> 13:48.995
[ chuckle ]

13:48.995 --> 13:50.997
‐ I've been waiting to ride the tunnel

13:50.997 --> 13:55.460
until I found a truly special friend
with whom I could share it.

13:55.752 --> 13:56.669
And then...

13:56.669 --> 13:57.754
along came Synth.

13:58.379 --> 14:00.506
‐ Ha! Man!

14:00.506 --> 14:04.635
This tunnel ride is gonna be
a‐meh‐meh‐meh‐mazing!

14:05.970 --> 14:08.639
I can not go in that tunnel with Minuet.

14:09.015 --> 14:09.849
‐ Huh?
‐ Huh?

14:09.849 --> 14:11.059
‐ Yeah, check it out:

14:11.476 --> 14:14.437
I'm kind of embarrassed to admit this,
but your boy Synth...

14:15.688 --> 14:16.939
is afraid of the dark.

14:17.607 --> 14:19.025
‐ Afraid of the dark?

14:19.358 --> 14:20.526
‐ Petrified, yo.

14:20.818 --> 14:23.279
Why do you think I always have
so many glow sticks?

14:26.866 --> 14:29.327
[ screaming ]

14:32.789 --> 14:35.541
You saw how excited
Minuet is for this ride,

14:35.875 --> 14:37.835
but the second I go in the dark,

14:37.835 --> 14:41.214
I'm totally gonna flip out
and ruin the special moment!

14:41.214 --> 14:45.301
‐ Aw, hush now.
It won't be as bad as all that, sugar.

14:45.593 --> 14:48.638
I mean, everyone gets
a little uneasy in the dark.

14:48.888 --> 14:52.350
‐ Oh, yeah?
When you're in the dark, do you do this?

14:52.767 --> 14:54.852
[ screaming ]

14:54.852 --> 14:58.022
[ panting ]

14:58.022 --> 15:00.399
[ deep breath ]

15:01.150 --> 15:01.984
[ gasp ]

15:04.028 --> 15:04.946
‐ Well...

15:04.946 --> 15:06.906
this here's a pickle, y'all.

15:07.198 --> 15:08.658
‐ I know!

15:08.658 --> 15:10.409
Just when you think you've learned

15:10.409 --> 15:13.496
all there is about Synth,
you uncover yet another facet

15:13.496 --> 15:14.705
to his personality.

15:14.997 --> 15:19.127
Argh, why must I be such a deep
and complex character, yo?

15:21.045 --> 15:22.171
‐ It'll be ok, Synth.

15:22.505 --> 15:26.259
I'm confident we will completely cure
your fear of the dark by tomorrow.

15:26.259 --> 15:27.176
‐ That's right.

15:27.468 --> 15:29.846
Sittin' in a dark tunnel
is no different than...

15:30.221 --> 15:31.889
closing your eyes when you sleep.

15:32.223 --> 15:34.267
‐ Oh, I sleep with my eyes open.

15:34.892 --> 15:36.519
It is deeply unsettling.

15:37.353 --> 15:41.399
‐ Okay, maybe we won't completely cure
your fear of the dark by tomorrow.

15:41.607 --> 15:44.402
But you only need
to tolerate it long enough

15:44.402 --> 15:46.737
for the tunnel ride, which is what?

15:47.029 --> 15:47.864
Three minutes?

15:48.030 --> 15:49.115
‐ At most!

15:49.323 --> 15:52.076
So all you gotta do is practice
with this sleep mask

15:52.076 --> 15:54.412
'til you can stand it for three minutes!

15:54.704 --> 15:56.289
‐ And when I was a little Troll,

15:56.539 --> 15:58.207
whenever I got scared of the dark,

15:58.207 --> 16:00.626
I'd squeeze my pillow and I felt better.

16:01.002 --> 16:03.045
‐ Oh, a security woobie?

16:03.462 --> 16:05.840
Ha, ha! <i>Noice!</i>

16:06.257 --> 16:08.342
‐ Well, let's give it a shot, y'all!

16:10.595 --> 16:16.601
[ grunting ]

16:19.604 --> 16:22.231
‐ Three minutes?
‐ Eight seconds.

16:22.231 --> 16:23.274
[ sigh ]

16:23.274 --> 16:25.735
‐ Yo. We're gonna need more woobies.

16:26.235 --> 16:28.029
POPPY:
How about a security pinata?

16:29.989 --> 16:31.490
‐ 47 seconds.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.326
POPPY:
A security melon?

16:33.326 --> 16:34.577
[ grunt ]

16:36.579 --> 16:38.664
‐ A minute twenty‐three.

16:38.664 --> 16:39.665
[ grunt ]

16:39.665 --> 16:41.000
POPPY:
A security rock?

16:41.000 --> 16:43.586
[ grunt ]

16:43.586 --> 16:44.420
[ gasps ]

16:44.420 --> 16:47.006
[ grunt ]

16:47.006 --> 16:50.259
3, 2, 1!

16:50.259 --> 16:51.510
Three minutes!

16:51.510 --> 16:53.429
‐ You did it, Synth!
‐ You did it, Synth!

16:53.846 --> 16:54.680
‐ I did?

16:54.931 --> 16:56.557
[ screaming ]

16:59.727 --> 17:00.561
‐ Heh...

17:01.520 --> 17:03.272
[ laugh ]

17:08.361 --> 17:09.737
‐ Ooh, here we go!

17:10.029 --> 17:11.280
‐ Heh‐heh, yep.

17:11.656 --> 17:12.823
Just you, me...

17:13.115 --> 17:14.325
and my lucky rock.

17:14.867 --> 17:17.078
STRIPE:
<i>This is it, you fast friends,</i>

17:17.078 --> 17:19.747
<i>you bosom buddies, you cherished chums,</i>

17:19.747 --> 17:22.541
<i>you most personal pals,</i>
<i>you sister and brother</i>

17:22.541 --> 17:24.794
<i>from a different mister and mother, you‐‐</i>

17:26.504 --> 17:27.380
Okay, I'll stop.

17:27.797 --> 17:29.090
Enjoy your ride!

17:29.674 --> 17:31.926
‐ Oh, this is it, Synth.

17:32.343 --> 17:33.177
‐ Yeah...

17:35.555 --> 17:36.806
This is it.

17:41.310 --> 17:42.520
‐ C'mon, Synth.

17:42.520 --> 17:45.273
Just hold it together for three minutes.

17:45.273 --> 17:47.191
‐ Ugh, I can't watch.

17:47.191 --> 17:48.693
‐ Neither can I!

17:51.529 --> 17:55.908
[ breathing heavily ]

17:55.908 --> 17:56.951
MINUET:
Synth?

17:57.785 --> 17:59.870
Thank you so much for doing this with me.

18:01.080 --> 18:04.166
‐ Well, yeah, Minuet,
I wouldn't let anything stop me

18:04.166 --> 18:06.794
from being here with you,
like anything, yo.

18:08.838 --> 18:14.844
♪

18:16.012 --> 18:17.930
♪ Don't it seem like you and me ♪

18:17.930 --> 18:20.057
♪ Were made to be the best of friends ♪

18:20.057 --> 18:21.892
♪ Much the same in many ways ♪

18:21.892 --> 18:23.936
♪ It over shines our difference ♪

18:23.936 --> 18:25.896
♪ Come along, let's sing a song ♪

18:25.896 --> 18:27.815
♪ About the ways that we are great ♪

18:27.815 --> 18:30.776
♪ Sing along and celebrate ♪

18:30.776 --> 18:32.194
♪ Yeah, I'm like the bread ♪

18:32.194 --> 18:34.113
♪ And I am like the jam ♪

18:34.447 --> 18:35.865
♪ Wherever you are ♪

18:35.865 --> 18:38.576
♪ Is exactly where I am ♪

18:38.576 --> 18:40.244
♪ Me and you cruising through ♪

18:40.244 --> 18:42.371
♪ Yeah, we're two of a kind ♪

18:42.371 --> 18:46.208
♪ And wherever we are
Gonna be a good time ♪

18:46.208 --> 18:48.169
♪ Me and you, letting lose ♪

18:48.169 --> 18:49.962
♪ Not a thing on our mind ♪

18:49.962 --> 18:53.799
♪ Yeah, whatever we do
Gonna be a good time ♪

18:53.799 --> 18:56.802
♪ Me and you ♪♪

18:58.262 --> 19:00.056
‐ I... I made it!

19:00.598 --> 19:01.807
‐ Yay!

19:02.391 --> 19:05.895
[ screaming ]

19:06.562 --> 19:08.356
Oh my. That's odd.

19:08.773 --> 19:11.359
‐ Yeah... We were so close to the light.

19:11.776 --> 19:13.819
I mean, the end!

19:14.111 --> 19:16.238
STRIPE:
<i>Apologies, guys and gals.</i>

19:16.238 --> 19:19.492
<i>It appears there's a monkey wrench</i>
<i>in our get‐up‐and‐go!</i>

19:19.492 --> 19:20.409
[ grunt ]

19:20.409 --> 19:21.786
<i>But have no fear...</i>

19:21.786 --> 19:22.828
[ grunt ]

19:22.828 --> 19:25.122
<i>Ol' Stripe will have you moving lickety‐‐</i>

19:25.122 --> 19:26.332
[ racket ]

19:26.332 --> 19:29.293
<i>Jeepers, Ol' Stripey</i>
<i>does not like that sound at all.</i>

19:29.877 --> 19:31.879
<i>What do you mean they can still hear me?</i>

19:31.879 --> 19:32.838
[ sigh ]

19:33.673 --> 19:35.591
‐ Oh, this is delightful.

19:35.883 --> 19:39.762
It appears our special moment
will last a few minutes more.

19:40.221 --> 19:41.681
‐ Minutes more?

19:45.351 --> 19:46.185
‐ Uh, oh.
‐ Uh, oh.

19:46.894 --> 19:49.146
[ heavy breathing ]

19:50.981 --> 19:53.609
‐ You know what?
I bet I can get us movin' again.

19:57.113 --> 19:57.947
There!

19:58.781 --> 20:04.745
[ screaming ]

20:04.745 --> 20:06.122
[ panting ]

20:06.122 --> 20:07.790
‐ Synth? Are you okay?

20:07.790 --> 20:09.750
‐ Who? Me? What?

20:09.750 --> 20:11.293
When? Where?

20:11.293 --> 20:12.670
And sometimes why!

20:12.670 --> 20:13.587
[ chuckle ]

20:13.587 --> 20:15.965
Oh, but I think I dropped my hug watch.

20:16.340 --> 20:17.883
Gonna grab a light real quick.

20:18.551 --> 20:19.427
[ chuckle ]

20:19.719 --> 20:20.636
Phew.

20:21.178 --> 20:22.096
Ah!

20:22.096 --> 20:24.473
Aw, c'mon!

20:24.473 --> 20:27.309
I thought we were ice cream buds, yo!

20:27.852 --> 20:30.312
[ panting ]

20:30.312 --> 20:32.773
‐ Synth, are you sure you're all right?

20:32.773 --> 20:33.983
You seem a little‐‐

20:33.983 --> 20:35.901
‐ Happy? 'Cuz that's what I am.

20:35.901 --> 20:36.819
[ chuckle ]

20:36.819 --> 20:39.613
Happy to share this once
in‐a‐lifetime moment with you!

20:40.698 --> 20:41.532
Ah!

20:44.827 --> 20:48.456
[ Synth screams ]

20:49.623 --> 20:50.499
[ gasp ]

20:50.499 --> 20:52.960
[ panting ]

20:52.960 --> 20:53.794
MINUET:
Synth?

20:54.587 --> 20:56.172
Why did you do all that?

20:56.505 --> 21:00.384
‐ Who? Me? What? When? Where?

21:00.384 --> 21:01.635
And sometimes‐‐
‐ Synth!

21:02.553 --> 21:03.387
[ sigh ]

21:04.054 --> 21:05.723
‐ Yeah, okay.

21:06.140 --> 21:07.933
The truth is I did all that 'cuz...

21:10.519 --> 21:11.645
I'm afraid of the dark.

21:13.230 --> 21:14.440
‐ Afraid of the dark?

21:16.525 --> 21:19.570
Of course,
that explains all those glowsticks.

21:20.196 --> 21:24.158
‐ Yeah. I thought I could overcome it,
but I came up short...

21:24.909 --> 21:27.995
and I ruined something
that was really important to you.

21:29.747 --> 21:30.581
‐ Oh...

21:30.956 --> 21:31.916
I see...

21:34.335 --> 21:35.336
Meh. No big deal.

21:37.004 --> 21:37.838
‐ "Meh"?

21:38.255 --> 21:39.799
But you were so excited...

21:40.466 --> 21:42.218
‐ Yes, I was...

21:42.718 --> 21:46.722
excited to experience
a very special moment...

21:47.681 --> 21:48.516
with you.

21:51.685 --> 21:55.397
"With you" is the part
that really matters to me, Synth.

21:55.981 --> 21:58.359
So, if you don't want
to ride the tunnel, well...

21:58.818 --> 21:59.652
neither do I.

22:00.444 --> 22:01.403
[ sniff ]

22:01.403 --> 22:02.238
‐ Yo.

22:04.406 --> 22:05.699
‐ Aww!
‐ Aww!

22:06.283 --> 22:08.911
‐ Besides, I'm sure there are

22:08.911 --> 22:12.706
plenty of ways to celebrate
a friendship in TrollsTopia...

22:12.957 --> 22:13.874
SYNTH:
Mmhmm.

22:14.667 --> 22:16.961
‐ Step right up! Step right up!

22:16.961 --> 22:21.924
To the very well illuminated,
open‐air, Gondola of Camaraderie!

22:23.259 --> 22:25.845
‐ Now this, this is something special.

22:26.262 --> 22:28.639
‐ Yeah, boy!

22:28.848 --> 22:30.307
[ laugh ]

22:31.642 --> 22:37.314
♪

22:38.607 --> 22:40.025
♪ Yeah, I'm like the bread ♪

22:40.025 --> 22:42.152
♪ And I am like the jam ♪

22:42.653 --> 22:43.988
♪ Wherever you are ♪

22:43.988 --> 22:46.657
♪ Is exactly where I am ♪

22:46.657 --> 22:48.450
♪ Me and you cruising through ♪

22:48.450 --> 22:50.452
♪ Yeah, we're two of a kind ♪

22:50.452 --> 22:54.290
♪ And wherever we are
Gonna be a good time ♪

22:54.290 --> 22:56.250
♪ Me and you, letting lose ♪

22:56.250 --> 22:58.210
♪ Not a thing on our mind ♪

22:58.210 --> 23:02.089
♪ Yeah, whatever we do
Gonna be a good time ♪

23:02.089 --> 23:04.967
♪ Me and you ♪♪
